Kentucky Derby Winner Animal Kingdom to Run in New York’s Belmont Stakes

-- B y   M i c h a e l   S i l l u p
-- 
2011-05-27T17:35:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/kentucky-derby-winner-animal-kingdom-to-run-in-new-york-s-belmont-stakes.html
Kentucky Derby winner  Animal Kingdom 
will run in the Belmont Stakes on June 11, the third leg of
horse racing’s Triple Crown.  Animal Kingdom won the Derby by 2 3/4 lengths and finished
second behind Shackleford in the  Preakness Stakes  in Baltimore
on May 21.  The Belmont is run at Belmont Park in Elmont,  New York . At
1 1/2 miles, it is the longest of the Triple Crown events.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  